#  JEUX

:: Overview
JEUX is a Python-based game project developed as part of our studies.  
The goal of this project was to design a simple but structured game, including a main menu, multiple levels, and interactive elements such as buttons, sounds, and graphical assets.


:: What the game includes
The project is built around several core components:
- A main menu allowing the player to start the game  
- Multiple levels with different configurations  
- Interactive buttons for navigation  
- Sound effects to enhance the experience  
- A Game Over system  
- A structured organization of assets and game logic  


:: Project structure
The project is organized to separate logic, assets, and game flow:
* levels/ Contains level data and configurations
* assets/ Images, sounds, and visual resources
* classes/ Game logic and object definitions
* main.py / Entry point of the game
* main_menu.py / Handles the main menu
*buttons.py / Manages button interactions

::Technologie
*This project was developed using:
         Python
::Purpose
This project allowed me to:
.Learn how to structure a complete Python project
.Work with game logic and user interaction
.Organize code into multiple files and components
.Improve my overall programming skills
